    • Method Detail

      • omitNullValues

        public Objects.ToStringHelper omitNullValues()
        Configures the Objects.ToStringHelper so Object.toString() will ignore properties with null value. The order of calling this method, relative to the add()/addValue() methods, is not significant.

      • add

        public Objects.ToStringHelper add(java.lang.String name,
                         java.lang.Object value)
        Adds a name/value pair to the formatted output in name=value format. If value is null, the string "null" is used, unless omitNullValues() is called, in which case this name/value pair will not be added.
